---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import StorefrontHero from '../components/StorefrontHero.astro';
import { APP_STORE_URL, DEMO_URL } from '../consts';

const title = 'QSortby — Smart Collection Sorting for Shopify';
const description =
  'QSortby reorders every Shopify collection in real time so your best-converting, in-stock products always meet shoppers first — selling more from the catalog you already have.';
---
<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <!-- ===================== HERO ===================== -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="wrap herogrid">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span> Built for Shopify</span>
        <h1><em>Sell more</em> from the <em>catalog</em> you already have.</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          QSortby reorders every collection by what's selling right now — your best products meet
          shoppers first, sold-out steps aside. No theme code.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-cta">
          <a href={DEMO_URL} class="btn btn-accent btn-lg">Book a demo <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg></a>
          <a href={APP_STORE_URL} class="btn btn-line btn-lg">Add to Shopify</a>
        </div>
        <p class="hero-note">No theme code · 7-day free trial · Live in minutes</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-viz"><StorefrontHero /></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== TRUST BAR ===================== -->
  <section style="padding:1rem 0 0">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="trustbar rv">
        <span class="ti"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 3l8 4v6c0 5-4 7-8 8-4-1-8-3-8-8V7z"/></svg> Built for Shopify</span>
        <span class="sep"></span>
        <span class="ti"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 2l8 4v6c0 5-4 8-8 10-4-2-8-5-8-10V6z"/><path d="M9 12l2 2 4-4"/></svg> GDPR-ready</span>
        <span class="sep"></span>
        <span class="ti"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="3" y="5" width="18" height="14" rx="2"/><path d="M3 10h18"/></svg> Shopify Billing</span>
        <span class="sep"></span>
        <span class="ti"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M13 2L3 14h7l-1 8 10-12h-7z"/></svg> Real-time</span>
        <span class="sep"></span>
        <span class="ti"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/><path d="M3 12h18"/></svg> No theme code</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== FEATURE BENTO ===================== -->
  <section class="sec alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="shead ctr rv" style="margin-bottom:2.5rem">
        <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span> The product</span>
        <h2>Sort, track, and <em>personalize</em> — automatically.</h2>
        <p class="lead-c">Rank every collection by the metrics that matter, track how shoppers really behave, and give each visitor a storefront tuned to them.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="fbento">
        <article class="fb wide rv">
          <div class="fb-txt">
            <span class="kicker">Smart auto-sort</span>
            <h3>Sort by any signal</h3>
            <p>Velocity, revenue, margin, conversion, trending — pick the signal and the collection orders itself.</p>
            <div class="chips">
              <span class="ch on">Best sellers</span><span class="ch">Revenue</span><span class="ch">Margin</span><span class="ch">Conversion</span><span class="ch">Trending</span><span class="ch">Selling fast</span><span class="ch">Repeat buyers</span><span class="ch">Engagement</span><span class="ch">Rating</span><span class="ch">Newest</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="fb-viz">
            <div class="anim-sort" aria-hidden="true">
              <div class="asr asr-a"><span class="th"><img src="/products/candle-amber.svg" alt="" /></span><span class="ln"></span><b>142</b></div>
              <div class="asr asr-b"><span class="th"><img src="/products/perfume-noir.svg" alt="" /></span><span class="ln"></span><b>118</b></div>
              <div class="asr asr-c"><span class="th"><img src="/products/oud-attar.svg" alt="" /></span><span class="ln"></span><b>97</b></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="fb rv">
          <span class="kicker">Real-time</span>
          <h3>Updates as sales land</h3>
          <p>Every order re-scores your catalog instantly.</p>
          <div class="fb-viz">
            <div class="anim-rt" aria-hidden="true">
              <span class="rt-live"><i></i> live</span>
              <div class="gcard rt-card">
                <span class="gthumb"><img src="/products/candle-amber.svg" alt="" /></span>
                <div class="rt-meta">
                  <span class="rt-nm">Amber Noir Candle</span>
                  <span class="rt-bar"><i></i></span>
                  <span class="rt-pip">+1</span>
                </div>
                <span class="rt-rank">#1</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="fb rv">
          <span class="kicker">Inventory-aware</span>
          <h3>Sold-out steps aside</h3>
          <p>Out-of-stock drops; restocks climb back.</p>
          <div class="fb-viz">
            <div class="anim-drop" aria-hidden="true">
              <div class="drow"><span class="th"><img src="/products/candle-amber.svg" alt="" /></span><span class="ln"></span><span class="pill ok">In stock</span></div>
              <div class="drow out"><span class="th"><img src="/products/diffuser-reed.svg" alt="" /></span><span class="ln"></span><span class="pill no">Sold out</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="fb rv">
          <span class="kicker">Full control</span>
          <h3>Override &amp; preview</h3>
          <p>Reorder or exclude products by hand — and preview the exact before/after diff before it goes live.</p>
          <div class="fb-viz">
            <div class="anim-drag" aria-hidden="true">
              <div class="grow"><span class="grip"></span><span class="th"><img src="/products/oud-attar.svg" alt="" /></span><span class="ln"></span></div>
              <div class="grow lift"><span class="grip"></span><span class="th"><img src="/products/perfume-noir.svg" alt="" /></span><span class="ln"></span><span class="pin">moved</span></div>
              <div class="grow"><span class="grip"></span><span class="th"><img src="/products/candle-amber.svg" alt="" /></span><span class="ln"></span></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="fb rv">
          <span class="kicker">Personalization</span>
          <h3>A "For You" feed per shopper</h3>
          <p>Classify visitors into types and give each its own ranking — a live, personalized feed.</p>
          <div class="fb-viz">
            <div class="anim-aud" aria-hidden="true">
              <div class="aud-tabs"><span class="atab a1">New</span><span class="atab a2">VIP</span></div>
              <div class="aud-list">
                <div class="gcard arow ra"><span class="gthumb"><img src="/products/candle-amber.svg" alt="" /></span><span class="rt-nm">Amber Noir Candle</span></div>
                <div class="gcard arow rb"><span class="gthumb"><img src="/products/perfume-noir.svg" alt="" /></span><span class="rt-nm">Noir Eau de Parfum</span></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="fb wide rv">
          <div class="fb-txt">
            <span class="kicker">Shopper tracking</span>
            <h3>Know why products move</h3>
            <p>A first-party pixel captures views, carts and journeys — funnels you can actually act on.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="fb-viz">
            <div class="anim-why" aria-hidden="true">
              <div class="gcard why-stage w1"><span class="why-k">Views</span><span class="why-v">1,240</span><span class="why-bar"><i style="--w:100%"></i></span></div>
              <span class="why-flow"></span>
              <div class="gcard why-stage w2"><span class="why-k">Carts</span><span class="why-v">384</span><span class="why-bar"><i style="--w:64%"></i></span></div>
              <span class="why-flow"></span>
              <div class="gcard why-stage w3"><span class="why-k">Sales</span><span class="why-v">96</span><span class="why-bar"><i style="--w:30%"></i></span></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="fb rv">
          <span class="kicker">Emotional AI <span class="soon">Beta</span></span>
          <h3>Read buyer intent</h3>
          <p>Emotional AI reads on-site signals to surface what each shopper is most likely to buy.</p>
          <div class="fb-viz">
            <div class="anim-int" aria-hidden="true">
              <div class="int-sigs"><span class="sig sg1">dwell</span><span class="sig sg2">revisit</span><span class="sig sg3">compare</span></div>
              <div class="int-meter"><i class="int-fill"></i></div>
              <span class="int-lbl">High intent</span>
              <div class="gcard int-rec"><span class="gthumb"><img src="/products/oud-attar.svg" alt="" /></span><span class="rt-nm">Midnight Oud</span><span class="int-tag">Show now</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== THE RANKING ENGINE ===================== -->
  <section class="sec alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="shead ctr rv" style="margin-bottom:2.5rem">
        <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span> The ranking engine</span>
        <h2>Ranked for conversion — and <em>proven</em>, not guessed.</h2>
        <p class="lead-c">No black box. You pick the signal, QSortby scores your catalog live and keeps in-stock first — or personalizes per shopper — then a built-in A/B test and revenue attribution prove how much it actually lifted.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="steps rv" style="margin-bottom:2.75rem">
        <div class="step">
          <div class="sn">01 · Choose</div>
          <h3>Pick the signal</h3>
          <p>Rank each collection by any of 10+ live signals — velocity, revenue, margin, conversion rate, trending momentum, selling-fast, repeat buyers, engagement, rating, newest — over a rolling or fixed window you set.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="sn">02 · Rank</div>
          <h3>Score live, in-stock first</h3>
          <p>Every order re-scores the catalog within seconds. Sold-out sinks to the bottom, restocks climb back — so shoppers only meet products they can actually buy.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="sn">03 · Prove</div>
          <h3>A/B it, keep the winner</h3>
          <p>Test any sort against your current order. QSortby measures clicks → cart → attributed revenue and calls statistical significance — so the winning sort is the one the data picks, not a guess.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="stats rv">
        <div class="s"><b><em>10+</em></b><span>ranking signals</span></div>
        <div class="s"><b>Real-time</b><span>re-scored every order</span></div>
        <div class="s"><b>A/B</b><span>tested for significance</span></div>
        <div class="s"><b>Attributed</b><span>revenue per sort</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== SETUP ===================== -->
  <section class="sec">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="shead rv" style="margin-bottom:2.5rem">
        <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span> Setup</span>
        <h2>Live in three steps.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step rv"><div class="sn">01</div><h3>Install</h3><p>Add QSortby from the App Store. No theme edits.</p></div>
        <div class="step rv"><div class="sn">02</div><h3>Pick a signal</h3><p>Choose how each collection sorts. Preview it.</p></div>
        <div class="step rv"><div class="sn">03</div><h3>It sorts itself</h3><p>Real-time ordering, sold-out demoted. Done.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== SOCIAL PROOF (placeholder for video testimonials) ===================== -->
  <section class="sec">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="shead ctr rv" style="margin-bottom:2.5rem">
        <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span> Merchants</span>
        <h2>Hear it from the stores.</h2>
      </div>
      <!-- PLACEHOLDER: swap each tile for a real merchant video testimonial before launch. -->
      <div class="vquotes rv">
        <div class="vq"><span class="play"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M8 5v14l11-7z"/></svg></span><span class="vlbl">Video testimonial</span><span class="vsub">Coming soon</span></div>
        <div class="vq"><span class="play"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M8 5v14l11-7z"/></svg></span><span class="vlbl">Video testimonial</span><span class="vsub">Coming soon</span></div>
        <div class="vq"><span class="play"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M8 5v14l11-7z"/></svg></span><span class="vlbl">Video testimonial</span><span class="vsub">Coming soon</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== PRICING TEASER (mock — finalize later) ===================== -->
  <section class="sec alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="shead ctr rv" style="margin-bottom:2.5rem">
        <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span> Pricing</span>
        <h2>Simple pricing. Free for 7 days.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="plans rv">
        <div class="plan">
          <span class="ptag">Starter</span>
          <div class="price"><b>$29</b><span>/ month</span></div>
          <p class="pdesc">A storefront that sorts and personalizes itself.</p>
          <a href="/pricing" class="btn btn-line w-full">Compare plans</a>
        </div>
        <div class="plan feat">
          <span class="badge">Most popular</span>
          <span class="ptag">Pro</span>
          <div class="price"><b>$99</b><span>/ month</span></div>
          <p class="pdesc">Unlimited scale, analytics &amp; Emotional AI (beta).</p>
          <a href={DEMO_URL} class="btn btn-accent w-full">Book a demo</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="kicker" style="text-align:center;margin-top:1.5rem">Placeholder pricing · final plans TBD</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== FAQ ===================== -->
  <section class="sec">
    <div class="narrow">
      <div class="shead ctr rv" style="margin-bottom:2.5rem">
        <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span> Questions</span>
        <h2>Good to know</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq rv">
        <details><summary>What algorithm does QSortby use to maximize conversion value?<span class="pm"></span></summary><div class="ans">There's no single black-box formula. You pick the ranking signal per collection — sales velocity, revenue, margin, <b>conversion rate</b>, trending momentum, selling-fast, repeat-purchase, engagement, rating or newest — and QSortby scores your catalog in real time, keeping in-stock products first. The part that answers "maximum conversion value": you can <b>A/B-test any sort against your current order</b>, and QSortby measures the funnel it drove (clicks → add-to-cart → <b>influenced revenue</b>, via last-touch attribution) and reports <b>statistical significance</b> — so the winning sort is the one the data proves, not a guess.</div></details>
        <details><summary>What can QSortby sort by?<span class="pm"></span></summary><div class="ans">10+ live signals: sales velocity, revenue (GMV), margin, conversion rate, trending momentum, selling-fast (velocity vs. remaining stock), repeat-purchase rate, engagement (clicks / CTR / dwell / add-to-cart), rating, or newest — over a rolling or fixed window you choose. Per-visitor "For You" ranking blends weighted signals per shopper. Or order any collection by hand.</div></details>
        <details><summary>How do I know it actually lifts sales?<span class="pm"></span></summary><div class="ans">QSortby runs an A/B test between the new sort and your current order, then attributes downstream orders (last-touch) to the feed a shopper interacted with — reporting click-through, add-to-cart and influenced revenue per variant with a significance verdict. You see the lift, you're not taking it on faith.</div></details>
        <details><summary>Do I need to edit my theme?<span class="pm"></span></summary><div class="ans">No. QSortby maintains standard Shopify collections — add them like any other. No custom code.</div></details>
        <details><summary>What happens when a product sells out?<span class="pm"></span></summary><div class="ans">It drops to the bottom automatically, and returns to its earned spot once restocked.</div></details>
        <details><summary>Is there a free trial?<span class="pm"></span></summary><div class="ans">Yes — 7 days, billed through Shopify's Billing API on your normal invoice.</div></details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== FINAL CTA ===================== -->
  <section class="sec" style="padding-top:0">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="cta rv">
        <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span> Get started</span>
        <h2>Let your storefront optimize itself for <em>higher conversion.</em></h2>
        <p>Book a 15-minute demo and watch QSortby re-sort your real collections in real time.</p>
        <div class="hero-cta" style="justify-content:center">
          <a href={DEMO_URL} class="btn btn-accent btn-lg">Book a demo <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg></a>
          <a href={APP_STORE_URL} class="btn btn-ghost btn-lg">Add to Shopify</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
